<br>
If I'd built the Wizard class I would have given the class ALL five types of damage (not DOTs, but poison and disease-based blasts) and make the resistances lower, not add in Lures then add monsters in with heinous resistances because Lures exist. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/01 12:19:29 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://wots-signatures.hypermart.net/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lures and resists</span><hr size=1> I think fire / ice works on Gullerback, Grim.<br>
